text: Isabelle Fack (born September 28, 1970) is a French water polo player. She was a member of the France women's national water polo team at the 2001 World Aquatics Championships and 2003 World Aquatics Championships. == References == == Other websites == * amber-stachowski-and-frances-isabelle-fack getty * frances-isabelle-fack-fights-for-the-ball getty * Water_Polo/Europe/Women_2001 todor Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:French water polo players
